Comment: The movie is alright, but what makes it bad to most viewers is, well, spolier alert, on the scenes where they're having party at a house in the beginning of the movies and the guys are at Vegas in a strip club while on their way to Area 51. These scenes just decreases the tone of horror and drama of all camara, documentary films, unless they provide evidence of all the events from the footages of real suspects. Next, the scene where they discover a cell where the alien pods are kept and before they saw them, they come across to variety of toys and children's clothes. This part made me questioned "Are there ghost children in Area 51, or the aliens were treated as children?" and also, I don't remember the military treating strange objects or people in the friendly and caring way. If they did have aliens, they would've left them in a cell with just pods and just treat them as experiments, instead of children. And last, but not least, the abduction scene where the group just went underground and into the light. But once they woke up after getting knocked out when proceeding into the light, they mysteriously end up getting abducted by a UFO on land and no longer underground, which trips my mind and vision. And I guess that's it what I think it might be wrong with the movie. TBH, I like horror, camera documentaries, but I don't like it when they take it to comedy from the beginning or throughout to horror at the end. Also, if there are horror cases the documentaries are showing, they should be accurate in how they are presenting when there are viewers, who know them real well.

Title: Area 51 Official Trailer 1 (2015) - Sci-Fi Horror Found Footage Movie HD
Comment:
Why was this not advertised for wider release in theaters like Paranormal Activity? It has an intriguing premise, some good ideas, and lacks jump scares (thank God). It's suspenseful, creepy (last act), and directed by Oren Peli who did Paranormal Activity. He tried something different and some of it works better than other parts. Some problems: 1.) Too much buildup. 2.) Shakey cam gets annoying in the last act. 3.) Payoff could have been better. 4.) The fate of two characters happens so quickly that if you blink, you'll miss it so PAY ATTENTION at the end of the scene where everything's WHITE. Even then, their fate is uncertain. BTW wikipedia the end if you're unsure. Overall, cool prep, sneak in, and exploration elements. On a more aware note, can we show more positive stuff with aliens? I get that Area 51 is a cool idea for a horror film, but almost every alien film seems to portray them as dark. Those interested in the trailer or topic may find something of interest here, but it's better to focus on the light, since "different races have different agendas" according to the highly respected, former Canadian Minister of Defense, Paul Hellyer (search him on youtube).¬†
C to a C+ from me.

Comment:
Oren Peli, though he's still attempting to push an overused subgenre, is still one of the better directors of modern horror. With an eye for visuals, tension, and a good sense of low budget production, his creation of the original Paranormal Activity was stellar. Some could argue that it was too slow paced or wasn't scary with it's use of jump scares, but it's quality of difference is that it brought fear into the general audience. It also was unique, and original, at the time. In the same sense as Spielberg's "Jaws", which made audiences afriad of the ocean, Peli's original "Activity" film brought fear to the bedroom.¬†

I have some expectations for this film. With Peli's direction I feel that, even though the film seems generic from this trailer, it might just have something unique within.

If not, then at least we'll get a good looking found footage horror. The visuals shown in this trailer look pretty okay in my opinion!
